This script audits important system directories by looping through a predefined list using a for loop. For each directory, it checks whether it exists and then retrieves its permissions, owner, and group using the ls -ld command combined with awk. The script also calculates the disk space usage using the du -sh command and extracts relevant output using cut. Additionally, it checks for the existence of a software configuration file (such as Git’s .gitconfig) and displays its permissions. This script demonstrates concepts like loops, conditional statements, and text processing using command-line utilities.

Script 4 — Log File Analyzer
